      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SENJUTSU (2) sat on the pace before tiring to be beaten 1.4 lengths resuming over 1300m at Hawkesbury last time out. Won at his only try second-up and won't find this as tough. Has more to give and take beating. MILES OF GLORY (7) returned from a spell in the same contest  beaten 2.75 lengths. Is well shy of her best and also finds a suitable assignment. HAZEL JEAN (5) improved last start finding a couple better over 1300m at Canberra. Best figures measure up and she has the inside gate and the blinkers on for the first time. Sure to run well. VILLA CASTINA (6) is back after a break and started the last campaign placing over 1400m at Hawkesbury. In good hands and one to consider. ",
